{
  "text": "The second category applies the cooperative coevolution (CC) framework [CITATION_1] . For example, the third-generation cooperative coevolutionary differential evolution algorithm [CITATION_2] maintains several independent subpopulations. Each subpopulation is a subset of the equal-length decision variables obtained by variable grouping (e.g., random grouping [CITATION_3] , linear grouping [CITATION_4] , ordered grouping [CITATION_5] , or differential grouping (DG) [CITATION_6] ). All the subpopulations work cooperatively to optimize the LSMOPs in a divide-and-conquer manner.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "54440970",
    "[CITATION_2]": "11968414",
